<h1>So what's all of this about, then?</h1>
<p class="lead">Glad you asked! Te Papa Culture Companion is a 'Web-based Companion App' for our Te Papa exhibits. In other words, it's a website that can accompany you on your smart phone, tablet, or laptop while you look around Te Papa, providing extra information, videos, audio snippets and additional material to complete your Te Papa experience. It can even make suggestions on what you might want to check out next!</p>

<h1>How does it work?</h1>
<p class="lead">Te Papa Culture Companion uses a range of different technologies to make it as easy as possible for you to get more information about each part of an exhibition. You'll find NFC tags, QR codes, and unique ID codes scattered around Te Papa which will take you to each different section of the web site.</p>

<!-- DIVE DEEPER -->
<h1>But why should you bother?</h1>
<p class="lead">Have you ever found a display in a museum that really gets you thinking? Something that interests you, something that you want to know more about? When we put together an exhibit, we selected some of the most important parts to show you, but there's so much more beneath the surface which we can't possibly fit! More stories, pictures, audio recordings and videos than you can sink your teeth into, and all in one easy-to-use online repository, ready at your fingertips for you to dive in.</p>

